This paper discusses the system architecture and key technologies for 5G heterogeneous cloud radio access networks, which are related to networking and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses signal processing and resource management, which are related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions self-organization and software-defined networks, which are related to control systems, making cs.AR (Robotics and Automation) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses cloud computing and energy harvesting, which are related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
